The paper proposes a method for root cause detection in complex distributed software systems using time series analysis. This involves tracking the propagation of effects when a given problem causes unaligned but homogeneous shifts of underlying states. This approach involves machine learning and data analysis techniques, which are commonly associated with the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.SE (Software Engineering). Additionally, the paper deals with time series data, which is a common topic in the sub-categories of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.DB (Databases).
